      {
        "content": "Social media platforms, designed for maximum engagement, often exploit psychological vulnerabilities, leading to addictive behaviors and impairing mental health. The endless scroll, likes, and notifications trigger dopamine responses similar to gambling, fostering dependency and anxiety. Moreover, curated feeds can create unrealistic standards and foster negative self-comparison, contributing to depression and low self-esteem. Cyberbullying and online harassment exacerbate these issues, creating environments that are often hostile rather than supportive. Implementing reforms such as transparent algorithms, moderation of harmful content, and tools to manage screen time can mitigate these impacts, fostering healthier digital environments for users.",
