      {
        "content": "Social media platforms often prioritize user data collection over privacy, employing algorithms that manipulate user behavior for profit. This exploitation of personal data without transparent consent leads to targeted advertising, misinformation, and breaches of trust. The pervasive surveillance not only infringes on individual privacy rights but also contributes to mental health issues by creating an environment of constant scrutiny and pressure to conform. Reforms focused on data protection, such as stronger privacy regulations and user control over data, are essential to safeguard both privacy and mental health, ensuring social media serves public interests rather than corporate agendas.",
        "additional_kwargs": {
          "refusal": null
