      {
        "content": "While social media indeed offers platforms for advocacy and connection, these benefits are countered by significant mental health challenges. The constant comparison fostered by curated feeds can lead to depression and anxiety, overshadowing positive interactions. The addictive nature of social media, driven by algorithms designed for maximum engagement, often results in excessive screen time that detracts from real-world relationships and activities. Furthermore, the prevalence of cyberbullying undermines the supportive community aspect, creating environments that can be detrimental to mental well-being. Reform is necessary to balance these impacts with the benefits you highlight.",
